---
name: scljet-write-index-deep
description: SclJet 3-level index B-tree — interior level itself overflows, so interior levels stack with promoted separators (cross-backend)
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet deep (3-level) index

3000 rows with a descending key `k`, index on `k`. The index needs ~60 leaves and
their separators overflow one interior page, so interior levels stack until a
single-page root — a genuine **3-level** index B-tree (root interior kind 2 → an
interior level → leaves kind 10). Verified out-of-band against reference SQLite
3.53.3: `integrity_check` cross-validates the multi-level index against the table,
the planner uses it (`SEARCH t USING COVERING INDEX`), and walking rightmost
children gives depth 3. Two-level output stays byte-identical to before.
Fingerprinted (iterative Adler-32) so int and JS must agree byte-for-byte.

[ByteSlice, byteSliceGet, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, buildTableWithIndexDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)

```scalascript
def buildRows(n: Int): List[List[SqliteValue]] =
  var brI = 0
  var brAcc: List[List[SqliteValue]] = Nil
  while brI < n do
    brAcc = List(SqlInteger((n - brI).toLong)) :: brAcc
    brI = brI + 1
  brAcc.reverse

def adler32(bytes: ByteSlice): Long =
  var adI = 0
  var adA = 1L
  var adB = 0L
  while adI < bytes.length do
    byteSliceGet(bytes, adI) match
      case Right(b) =>
        adA = (adA + b.toLong) % 65521L
        adB = (adB + adA) % 65521L
      case Left(e) => adA = adA
    adI = adI + 1
  adB * 65536L + adA

buildTableWithIndexDatabase(512, 1, 1, "t", "CREATE TABLE t(k INTEGER)",
  "by_k", "CREATE INDEX by_k ON t(k)", List(0), buildRows(3000)) match
  case Right(bytes) => println((bytes.length / 512).toString + ":" + bytes.length.toString + ":" + adler32(bytes).toString)
  case Left(error) => println("ERROR:" + error.message)
```
